1
00:00:04,871 --> 00:00:06,206
In 2026,

2
00:00:07,140 --> 00:00:10,243
I, Kosei Neo, president of NEOXIS,

3
00:00:10,810 --> 00:00:15,482
should have died when someone pushed me…

4
00:00:15,548 --> 00:00:19,152
I ended up in the body of Eito Nomoto,
who was supposed to have died

5
00:00:19,219 --> 00:00:22,255
in an accident in 2012.

6
00:00:22,322 --> 00:00:24,491
He was the son of Eiji Nomoto.

7
00:00:26,092 --> 00:00:30,163
The land Kosei Neo targeted
for NEOXIS's expansion was

8
00:00:30,830 --> 00:00:33,333
the Akari Shopping Street
and Akari Housing Complex.

9
00:00:34,401 --> 00:00:38,238
That was Eito Nomoto's hometown.

10
00:00:39,339 --> 00:00:41,441
<i>To prevent the tragedy
that was meant to happen,</i>

11
00:00:42,008 --> 00:00:44,377
I used Kosei Neo's memories

12
00:00:44,944 --> 00:00:47,580
to try and change the future. And…

13
00:00:47,647 --> 00:00:49,282
He's breathing! Call an ambulance!

14
00:00:49,349 --> 00:00:50,817
I dreamed we were all getting excited

15
00:00:51,384 --> 00:00:53,086
about starting over together.

16
00:00:53,153 --> 00:00:56,189
At last, the future has changed.

17
00:01:01,494 --> 00:01:05,899
But this book says this…

18
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:09,569
"Those who changed history

19
00:01:09,636 --> 00:01:12,405
and achieved success
will have to pay the price."

20
00:01:12,472 --> 00:01:14,274
"The price…

21
00:01:16,276 --> 00:01:17,310
is one's life."

22
00:01:17,377 --> 00:01:18,978
CHANGING HISTORY COSTS YOU YOUR LIFE

23
00:01:23,216 --> 00:01:24,884
Why is Kosei Neo pushing me

24
00:01:26,753 --> 00:01:28,888
to the edge like this?

25
00:01:29,789 --> 00:01:30,924
And…

26
00:01:33,359 --> 00:01:35,395
who

27
00:01:36,162 --> 00:01:37,197
killed me?

28
00:01:42,535 --> 00:01:44,003
February 17th, 2026.

29
00:01:44,070 --> 00:01:47,907
The fateful day of the fall

30
00:01:49,142 --> 00:01:50,376
is almost here.

31
00:01:53,213 --> 00:01:55,582
Hey! You can't be serious!

32
00:01:56,149 --> 00:01:59,152
The plan to move everyone
to the Super Soman site…

33
00:02:00,153 --> 00:02:02,188
How can it just be gone?!

34
00:02:03,089 --> 00:02:05,024
The Super Soman site

35
00:02:05,825 --> 00:02:09,362
was bought by President Neo of NEOXIS.

36
00:02:12,098 --> 00:02:14,667
I'm sorry, Kinpei.
Right after you got out of the hospital…

37
00:02:15,502 --> 00:02:18,204
Don't apologize. Everyone knows

38
00:02:18,271 --> 00:02:19,806
how hard you tried. Right?

39
00:02:21,474 --> 00:02:22,976
But what do we do now?

40
00:02:24,744 --> 00:02:27,447
I've been thinking hard
about what you said, Hideko.

41
00:02:28,581 --> 00:02:30,650
I can't keep tying down
Inose and the others,

42
00:02:31,417 --> 00:02:34,954
who have their futures ahead of them,
to a street with no work.

43
00:02:37,524 --> 00:02:38,658
You're right.

44
00:02:39,325 --> 00:02:42,195
We each have to find our own paths now.

45
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:46,332
So we're going to accept the eviction?

46
00:02:48,067 --> 00:02:48,902
That's right.

47
00:02:51,538 --> 00:02:54,974
We'll have enough time
before we have to leave.

48
00:02:56,409 --> 00:02:58,211
Let's use that time
to find somewhere to go

49
00:02:58,811 --> 00:03:01,581
and face our new futures.

50
00:03:04,117 --> 00:03:05,318
Hey,

51
00:03:05,385 --> 00:03:08,288
if we want to see each other,
we can meet up anytime.

52
00:03:08,354 --> 00:03:09,422
That's true.

53
00:03:09,489 --> 00:03:13,259
Come on! We'll still be friends, won't we?

54
00:03:15,628 --> 00:03:16,663
Then,

55
00:03:17,864 --> 00:03:19,265
Akari Shopping Street

56
00:03:20,934 --> 00:03:22,902
accepts the eviction.

57
00:03:29,342 --> 00:03:30,610
- See you!
- Take care!

58
00:03:30,677 --> 00:03:31,678
Take care of yourself.

59
00:03:31,744 --> 00:03:34,380
- Yes!
- Don't drink too much, Kinpei.

60
00:03:34,447 --> 00:03:35,882
Mind your own business.

61
00:03:35,949 --> 00:03:37,584
- Come visit, okay?
- Yes!

62
00:03:37,650 --> 00:03:39,352
- Come back soon.
- Be well!

63
00:03:39,419 --> 00:03:40,687
- Thanks!
- See you!

64
00:03:40,753 --> 00:03:43,489
- Take care!
- See you!

65
00:03:43,556 --> 00:03:44,691
See you!

66
00:03:47,594 --> 00:03:48,494
They're gone.

67
00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:51,464
Don't cry.

68
00:03:52,232 --> 00:03:53,066
Hey!

69
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:55,435
<i>And one by one,</i>

70
00:03:55,501 --> 00:03:58,204
<i>people left the shopping street.</i>

71
00:03:59,539 --> 00:04:01,641
<i>As the evictions continued</i>

72
00:04:01,708 --> 00:04:04,010
<i>into January 2026…</i>

73
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:10,650
Hideko and Kinpei
have both found work, apparently.

74
00:04:11,384 --> 00:04:12,318
I know.

75
00:04:12,885 --> 00:04:15,521
<i>She's straining her back
in a cramped food truck,</i>

76
00:04:15,588 --> 00:04:18,157
<i>and he's doing night security work.</i>

77
00:04:18,224 --> 00:04:20,360
Everyone's struggling
with work they're not used to.

78
00:04:24,464 --> 00:04:26,933
What about you, Dad?

79
00:04:28,534 --> 00:04:29,469
Never mind me.

80
00:04:29,535 --> 00:04:31,904
- Think about yourself…
- <i>The rising IT company NEOXIS…</i>

81
00:04:32,972 --> 00:04:35,908
<i>Kosei Neo, who founded the company</i>

82
00:04:36,476 --> 00:04:38,444
<i>under the "For the People" banner.</i>

83
00:04:38,511 --> 00:04:40,680
<i>In just seven years…</i>

84
00:04:40,747 --> 00:04:42,582
<i>In exchange for the Akari Shopping Street</i>

85
00:04:42,649 --> 00:04:44,784
<i>and Akari Housing Complex…</i>

86
00:04:46,352 --> 00:04:48,388
<i>…Kosei Neo</i>

87
00:04:48,454 --> 00:04:49,956
<i>now owns a bank.</i>

88
00:04:51,257 --> 00:04:54,494
It seems my eye for talent in backing you

89
00:04:55,728 --> 00:04:57,397
was not mistaken.

90
00:05:00,233 --> 00:05:01,234
Now that

91
00:05:01,901 --> 00:05:03,970
you're a bank owner,

92
00:05:04,037 --> 00:05:06,005
there's someone I'd like you to meet.

93
00:05:08,207 --> 00:05:09,676
A man

94
00:05:09,742 --> 00:05:12,245
who respects
your "For the People" philosophy

95
00:05:13,179 --> 00:05:14,747
and, following your example,

96
00:05:15,515 --> 00:05:18,618
founded a humanitarian support company.

97
00:05:24,424 --> 00:05:25,692
Tatsuki Tomono.

98
00:05:25,758 --> 00:05:26,592
‎FRIENDS EARTH SUPPORT
‎PRESIDENT TATSUKI TOMONO

99
00:05:27,427 --> 00:05:31,030
He says he has a request
to make of you in person.

100
00:05:32,699 --> 00:05:34,167
So in the end,

101
00:05:37,570 --> 00:05:39,539
when they're in trouble, they come to me.

102
00:05:45,511 --> 00:05:46,646
Sarasa.

103
00:05:49,515 --> 00:05:50,850
You've been at that for a long time.

104
00:05:50,917 --> 00:05:55,254
I have to paint this
before the shopping street is torn down.

105
00:05:57,790 --> 00:06:00,293
I've got sweet potato chips.

106
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,361
Let's take a tea break.

107
00:06:02,995 --> 00:06:05,698
You brought sweet potato chips
that time too.

108
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:07,667
Huh?

109
00:06:08,568 --> 00:06:10,169
You don't remember?

110
00:06:10,236 --> 00:06:14,474
The day you protected me
from that accident?

111
00:06:20,713 --> 00:06:22,014
Oh, right.

112
00:06:26,853 --> 00:06:29,088
Do you remember this painting?

113
00:06:29,155 --> 00:06:29,989
Yeah.

114
00:06:30,957 --> 00:06:32,825
When you were painting this,

115
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:36,429
<i>the sunset was so beautiful.</i>

116
00:06:37,029 --> 00:06:38,431
<i>It feels so nostalgic.</i>

117
00:06:39,165 --> 00:06:40,700
<i>Doesn't it?</i>

118
00:06:44,036 --> 00:06:45,538
This painting…

119
00:06:47,073 --> 00:06:48,641
Can you tell what this moment was?

120
00:06:53,679 --> 00:06:56,015
Even if you ask me
when it was supposed to be…

121
00:06:56,082 --> 00:06:58,284
The day we found a rainbow together.

122
00:06:59,218 --> 00:07:02,588
You don't remember the day
you proposed to me?

123
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:10,229
You remember this painting

124
00:07:10,863 --> 00:07:14,534
but not the day you proposed…

125
00:07:18,738 --> 00:07:21,340
Who are you?

126
00:07:23,976 --> 00:07:25,178
<i>That had been</i>

127
00:07:26,245 --> 00:07:27,847
<i>the unanswerable question</i>

128
00:07:28,381 --> 00:07:30,082
<i>haunting me all along.</i>

129
00:07:32,018 --> 00:07:33,419
I'm home.

130
00:07:34,387 --> 00:07:35,321
Hey.

131
00:07:36,389 --> 00:07:38,357
What's going on?
Coming home out of the blue?

132
00:07:38,424 --> 00:07:41,060
- Weren't you doing disaster relief?
- Thanks.

133
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:42,628
- In Hokuriku, right?
- Yeah.

134
00:07:42,695 --> 00:07:45,398
We came to Tokyo

135
00:07:45,965 --> 00:07:47,600
to ask for support for that work.

136
00:07:48,801 --> 00:07:50,870
Where are you asking

137
00:07:50,937 --> 00:07:51,771
for that support?

138
00:07:53,372 --> 00:07:54,874
Well…

139
00:07:55,641 --> 00:07:56,476
Kosei Neo.

140
00:07:58,744 --> 00:08:00,847
How did you know?

141
00:08:02,381 --> 00:08:03,349
No…

142
00:08:03,950 --> 00:08:06,085
Once the bank acquisition settles down,

143
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:09,622
I believe he'll return to who he was.

144
00:08:11,224 --> 00:08:12,925
<i>This is not good.</i>

145
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:15,962
<i>In my past-life memories,</i>

146
00:08:16,028 --> 00:08:18,831
<i>I was pushed by someone</i>

147
00:08:19,432 --> 00:08:21,567
<i>on the morning of February 17th</i>

148
00:08:21,634 --> 00:08:23,102
<i>when Japan was gripped with excitement</i>

149
00:08:23,169 --> 00:08:25,371
<i>over the Milano Cortina Olympics.</i>

150
00:08:57,136 --> 00:08:58,104
At last…

151
00:09:00,239 --> 00:09:01,807
the future of that day is coming.

152
00:09:12,952 --> 00:09:14,987
I can't believe this!

153
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:18,291
That's an outrageous sum.

154
00:09:18,925 --> 00:09:20,927
I can't believe Vena Bank

155
00:09:20,993 --> 00:09:22,962
had such enormous hidden liabilities.

156
00:09:23,629 --> 00:09:25,264
As the person in charge,

157
00:09:25,331 --> 00:09:26,832
I'm sorry for not catching this.

158
00:09:29,435 --> 00:09:32,305
Takarabe, don't expect
a severance package.

159
00:09:33,773 --> 00:09:35,541
Are you dismissing me?

160
00:09:37,577 --> 00:09:38,578
I'm sorry.

161
00:09:39,378 --> 00:09:41,847
This is my fault
for failing to see through you.

162
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:44,584
I am truly sorry.

163
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:56,062
What are we going to do, sir?

164
00:09:56,128 --> 00:09:59,432
This debt is enough
to threaten the company's survival.

165
00:09:59,498 --> 00:10:01,033
It'll be fine.

166
00:10:02,068 --> 00:10:04,270
Do you understand the situation?

167
00:10:04,337 --> 00:10:05,571
We're losing

168
00:10:05,638 --> 00:10:08,507
the public's trust
as well as everything else.

169
00:10:13,079 --> 00:10:17,483
We're covered in graffiti
and called murderers.

170
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:20,386
Can't you see that as a badge of honor

171
00:10:20,453 --> 00:10:22,555
for everything we've accomplished?

172
00:10:27,627 --> 00:10:28,761
I can't

173
00:10:30,062 --> 00:10:31,364
follow you anymore.

174
00:10:34,266 --> 00:10:35,368
That's a shame.

175
00:10:41,173 --> 00:10:42,608
Thank you for everything.

176
00:10:55,254 --> 00:10:56,188
Excuse me.

177
00:10:57,089 --> 00:10:59,558
The president of Friends Earth Support,
Tomono, is here.

178
00:11:01,193 --> 00:11:02,795
It's been a long time.

179
00:11:04,697 --> 00:11:05,731
Tomono.

180
00:11:06,832 --> 00:11:10,936
I was just thinking about you.

181
00:11:11,971 --> 00:11:14,006
The days we worked together
on disaster relief

182
00:11:14,073 --> 00:11:16,842
when you were part of the founding team…

183
00:11:19,245 --> 00:11:23,282
Your principles and drive back then

184
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:24,917
shaped who I became.

185
00:11:24,984 --> 00:11:27,520
I've never forgotten that.

186
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:32,224
So does that mean you'll work

187
00:11:32,792 --> 00:11:34,360
with me again?

188
00:11:35,428 --> 00:11:36,896
For that to happen,

189
00:11:36,962 --> 00:11:38,964
I first need you to support

190
00:11:39,031 --> 00:11:41,400
the Noto recovery efforts.

191
00:11:49,742 --> 00:11:52,144
You're still stuck there?

192
00:11:53,179 --> 00:11:56,515
- Huh?
- You haven't changed at all.

193
00:11:57,950 --> 00:11:59,618
You haven't grown one bit.

194
00:12:01,554 --> 00:12:04,490
Disaster support is important

195
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:05,791
and one of my principles.

196
00:12:05,858 --> 00:12:08,794
But you can't cling to that!

197
00:12:11,864 --> 00:12:15,034
I've told you many times.

198
00:12:15,101 --> 00:12:16,635
We're on a completely different stage now.

199
00:12:19,538 --> 00:12:21,707
You've really changed.

200
00:12:23,909 --> 00:12:25,411
You've abandoned your principles

201
00:12:26,412 --> 00:12:28,881
and have been consumed by ambition.

202
00:12:30,216 --> 00:12:32,218
You still don't see it.

203
00:12:37,523 --> 00:12:38,924
Excuse me.

204
00:12:54,106 --> 00:12:55,374
NEOXIS'S CRIMES, SABOTAGED AKARI
SHOPPING STREET'S SUPPLY AND ORDERS

205
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:56,642
Excuse me.

206
00:12:56,709 --> 00:12:58,210
Welcome.

207
00:12:58,277 --> 00:13:00,412
Please take care of the customer.

208
00:13:00,479 --> 00:13:01,514
Yes.

209
00:13:02,081 --> 00:13:03,883
Welcome. What can I get you?

210
00:13:03,949 --> 00:13:05,518
One rice ball please.

211
00:13:05,584 --> 00:13:07,319
Not you again.

212
00:13:07,386 --> 00:13:09,255
The customer before you was here first--

213
00:13:09,321 --> 00:13:10,289
- One rice ball please.
- Hey.

214
00:13:10,356 --> 00:13:11,557
Please don't cut in line.

215
00:13:11,624 --> 00:13:13,292
But I'm a customer too!

216
00:13:13,359 --> 00:13:14,460
Shut up!

217
00:13:15,361 --> 00:13:16,362
Get out of here!

218
00:13:17,163 --> 00:13:18,097
And don't come back!

219
00:13:18,164 --> 00:13:20,399
NEOXIS'S CRIMES, SABOTAGED AKARI
SHOPPING STREET'S SUPPLY AND ORDERS

220
00:13:26,338 --> 00:13:29,241
Hey, wait! Did you get permission?

221
00:13:31,710 --> 00:13:34,280
Hey! You can't just barge in! Get out!

222
00:13:34,346 --> 00:13:36,048
- Get out!
- What did you say?

223
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:39,518
"The end of Kosei Neo."

224
00:13:41,554 --> 00:13:42,988
"A fallen charismatic leader."

225
00:13:45,157 --> 00:13:46,492
"Cold-blooded."

226
00:13:48,727 --> 00:13:50,362
"Rot in hell."

227
00:13:59,371 --> 00:14:00,806
<i>I see.</i>

228
00:14:00,873 --> 00:14:04,643
So the request
for Kosei Neo's support didn't go well.

229
00:14:06,045 --> 00:14:09,348
Tomono felt there was no point
talking to him anymore.

230
00:14:12,184 --> 00:14:14,720
You've started your own company now.

231
00:14:14,787 --> 00:14:16,989
Just build a new life there.

232
00:14:17,056 --> 00:14:18,324
Yeah.

233
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:20,292
I think that's right.

234
00:14:22,127 --> 00:14:23,596
I've been thinking…

235
00:14:24,897 --> 00:14:27,766
Maybe no one person is truly to blame

236
00:14:27,833 --> 00:14:29,101
for how things turned out.

237
00:14:32,805 --> 00:14:33,639
You're right.

238
00:14:35,708 --> 00:14:37,443
What will you do now?

239
00:14:37,509 --> 00:14:39,578
We're meeting with a support organization

240
00:14:39,645 --> 00:14:41,714
that Togo introduced

241
00:14:41,780 --> 00:14:44,149
and then heading back
to the Hokuriku area tomorrow.

242
00:14:44,850 --> 00:14:45,951
I see.

243
00:14:49,655 --> 00:14:51,323
No matter what happens,

244
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:53,359
the two of you should keep
moving forward together.

245
00:14:55,461 --> 00:14:56,362
Yeah.

246
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:02,501
<i>Hearing that Tomono was leaving Tokyo,</i>

247
00:15:03,469 --> 00:15:04,937
<i>I felt relieved.</i>

248
00:15:11,777 --> 00:15:15,915
‎RICE WINE

249
00:15:17,082 --> 00:15:18,250
Long time no see.

250
00:15:18,317 --> 00:15:19,818
I'm Ichimanda from Soman.

251
00:15:20,452 --> 00:15:21,987
President Ichimanda…

252
00:15:22,821 --> 00:15:24,623
Togo has filled me in.

253
00:15:25,424 --> 00:15:26,425
You're not saying

254
00:15:26,492 --> 00:15:29,595
we'd let Soman swallow us up?

255
00:15:29,662 --> 00:15:32,364
That's one option on the table.

256
00:15:37,703 --> 00:15:40,339
Have we really caused you
that much concern?

257
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:43,676
If you insist,

258
00:15:43,742 --> 00:15:46,445
as the top company,
we can certainly throw a lifeline

259
00:15:46,512 --> 00:15:48,347
to a struggling peer.

260
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:52,117
Would it be all right if I declined?

261
00:15:53,118 --> 00:15:54,086
Sure.

262
00:15:55,487 --> 00:15:57,323
You're something else, Neo.

263
00:15:58,490 --> 00:16:01,560
Still running full speed
on a sinking ship.

264
00:16:03,295 --> 00:16:05,764
You've completely misread
the situation, Togo.

265
00:16:08,734 --> 00:16:09,835
Ichimanda.

266
00:16:10,736 --> 00:16:12,538
Regarding the generative AI leader

267
00:16:12,604 --> 00:16:15,407
Spread AI, which you've been courting,

268
00:16:15,474 --> 00:16:17,476
robotic and AI development

269
00:16:17,543 --> 00:16:20,679
<i>will now proceed jointly with our company.</i>

270
00:16:21,447 --> 00:16:25,050
We finalized that contract today.

271
00:16:26,185 --> 00:16:27,019
No way.

272
00:16:27,086 --> 00:16:31,357
That gives us a foothold
for fundraising, doesn't it, Togo?

273
00:16:32,524 --> 00:16:34,226
When did you manage to…

274
00:16:36,128 --> 00:16:38,831
Wouldn't you have been better off
getting on board our ship?

275
00:16:40,532 --> 00:16:41,667
If you'd like,

276
00:16:42,634 --> 00:16:45,304
I'll have a seat ready for you.

277
00:16:46,739 --> 00:16:48,140
Ichimanda,

278
00:16:48,207 --> 00:16:50,909
thank you for making the trip.

279
00:16:51,877 --> 00:16:52,911
Excuse me.

280
00:16:58,751 --> 00:17:00,619
Shall we head to the office?

281
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:06,825
It's finally

282
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:10,262
all over.

283
00:17:14,833 --> 00:17:16,135
Take me anywhere.

284
00:17:17,069 --> 00:17:18,971
Can you just drive for a while?

285
00:17:19,571 --> 00:17:20,706
Understood.

286
00:17:35,921 --> 00:17:38,891
<i>Who are you?</i>

287
00:17:50,102 --> 00:17:51,737
Everyone's headed home.

288
00:17:51,804 --> 00:17:54,239
The people at the disaster site
were so grateful…

289
00:17:56,208 --> 00:17:57,776
What's wrong?

290
00:17:57,843 --> 00:17:58,877
No…

291
00:18:01,613 --> 00:18:03,415
It might be my fault.

292
00:18:03,482 --> 00:18:05,017
If I'd handled things better,

293
00:18:06,218 --> 00:18:08,220
maybe I could have

294
00:18:08,787 --> 00:18:10,789
protected everyone…

295
00:18:13,425 --> 00:18:15,094
in Akari Shopping Street.

296
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:17,262
When I think about that, I…

297
00:18:18,831 --> 00:18:21,467
Don't be so hard on yourself.

298
00:18:22,201 --> 00:18:23,836
It's not your fault.

299
00:18:26,805 --> 00:18:29,108
What happened to the shopping street

300
00:18:30,676 --> 00:18:32,244
was due to President Neo.

301
00:18:36,248 --> 00:18:37,516
I'm excited.

302
00:18:38,083 --> 00:18:40,652
I have a feeling a new stage is beginning.

303
00:18:40,719 --> 00:18:43,989
<i>Shouldn't you look back at yourself
before all that?</i>

304
00:18:44,690 --> 00:18:46,492
Look back at myself? Me?

305
00:18:47,292 --> 00:18:50,729
<i>You've risen
by exploiting people's misfortune</i>

306
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:53,332
<i>and have built on people's sacrifices.</i>

307
00:18:53,398 --> 00:18:55,400
<i>That's my analysis.</i>

308
00:18:58,036 --> 00:18:59,771
Amazing.

309
00:18:59,838 --> 00:19:01,540
That's a sharp observation.

310
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:03,609
<i>Thank you.</i>

311
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:07,946
But I think you're overlooking one thing.

312
00:19:09,815 --> 00:19:11,950
Even if there are small sacrifices,

313
00:19:12,017 --> 00:19:16,221
my actions may save far more people.

314
00:19:17,156 --> 00:19:18,490
<i>You're lonely, aren't you?</i>

315
00:19:19,091 --> 00:19:20,993
No, I'm not.

316
00:19:21,059 --> 00:19:22,561
Because I have you.

317
00:20:12,678 --> 00:20:14,046
<i>And the fateful morning</i>

318
00:20:14,913 --> 00:20:17,983
<i>of February 17th arrived.</i>

319
00:20:23,789 --> 00:20:24,790
Hello?

320
00:20:24,856 --> 00:20:26,725
What is it, Eri? It's so early.

321
00:20:27,492 --> 00:20:28,860
Tomono's gone.

322
00:20:28,927 --> 00:20:30,395
He's not at the apartment, office,

323
00:20:30,462 --> 00:20:31,797
or the disaster relief office.

324
00:20:31,863 --> 00:20:33,198
I can't reach him.

325
00:20:33,932 --> 00:20:34,967
Huh?

326
00:20:35,601 --> 00:20:37,202
I'm scared.

327
00:20:37,269 --> 00:20:41,473
He's been drinking and blaming himself
for the shopping street's collapse.

328
00:20:41,540 --> 00:20:42,975
In his sleep,

329
00:20:43,041 --> 00:20:45,544
he was moaning
about not being able to forgive himself.

330
00:20:45,611 --> 00:20:46,945
Got it.

331
00:20:47,012 --> 00:20:48,046
Thanks.

332
00:20:53,418 --> 00:20:55,621
<i>Could it have been Tomono after all?</i>

333
00:21:01,927 --> 00:21:03,128
<i>Then I have to stop him,</i>

334
00:21:03,862 --> 00:21:04,896
<i>no matter what.</i>

335
00:21:16,775 --> 00:21:18,277
<i>This hasn't happened in a while…</i>

336
00:21:19,845 --> 00:21:21,046
<i>Why at this time…</i>

337
00:21:44,169 --> 00:21:45,270
The future…

338
00:22:20,038 --> 00:22:20,939
Tomono.

339
00:22:22,741 --> 00:22:23,975
Sir.

340
00:22:26,878 --> 00:22:28,180
I came to ask you

341
00:22:28,780 --> 00:22:30,515
to hear me out one last time.

342
00:22:31,650 --> 00:22:32,951
You sure are persistent.

343
00:22:33,018 --> 00:22:34,553
I've learned from you.

344
00:22:36,054 --> 00:22:40,192
I've learned everything from you.

345
00:22:41,059 --> 00:22:43,495
The principle of "For the People"
is everything.

346
00:22:44,162 --> 00:22:45,464
Yet…

347
00:22:46,565 --> 00:22:48,367
you changed.

348
00:22:49,167 --> 00:22:50,402
Why?

349
00:22:53,372 --> 00:22:56,475
You really don't understand,
do you, Tomono?

350
00:22:58,477 --> 00:23:01,346
If even you, who were so close to me
doesn't understand,

351
00:23:02,447 --> 00:23:04,583
then no one ever will.

352
00:23:05,784 --> 00:23:08,987
Why? I should be asking you that.

353
00:23:12,357 --> 00:23:13,358
Anyway,

354
00:23:14,559 --> 00:23:16,395
don't come near me anymore.

355
00:23:17,129 --> 00:23:19,664
You and I have parted ways.

356
00:23:29,007 --> 00:23:30,842
Eito, why are you here?

357
00:23:30,909 --> 00:23:32,744
I came to help you.

358
00:23:32,811 --> 00:23:35,213
I want to save Akari Shopping Street!

359
00:23:37,115 --> 00:23:39,251
Even if he dies, nothing will change.

360
00:23:47,325 --> 00:23:48,493
So, we finally meet.

361
00:23:53,298 --> 00:23:55,267
I didn't want to meet you.

362
00:23:57,736 --> 00:23:59,271
I was afraid of you.

363
00:24:02,340 --> 00:24:04,242
I feared that my existence

364
00:24:05,310 --> 00:24:08,280
would one day be replaced by yours.

365
00:24:10,515 --> 00:24:11,616
That frightened me.

366
00:24:13,251 --> 00:24:14,319
Because…

367
00:24:17,055 --> 00:24:19,124
you are Kosei Neo, right?

368
00:24:39,711 --> 00:24:42,113
It was so I could live on in a new place.

369
00:24:42,180 --> 00:24:43,815
- Eito!
- Eito!

370
00:24:45,650 --> 00:24:47,452
<i>Until I learned Eito Nomoto's past…</i>

371
00:24:49,321 --> 00:24:51,590
<i>and lived as Eito Nomoto…</i>

372
00:24:51,656 --> 00:24:53,959
<i>Absolutely outstanding.</i>

373
00:24:54,025 --> 00:24:55,327
- <i>Good, right?</i>
- Absolutely outstanding!

374
00:24:55,393 --> 00:24:56,228
<i>I…</i>

375
00:24:57,028 --> 00:24:59,364
began to lose track of who I really was.

376
00:25:01,199 --> 00:25:02,267
Maybe

377
00:25:04,069 --> 00:25:07,105
I had become Eito Nomoto himself.

378
00:25:10,242 --> 00:25:11,710
Living as Eito Nomoto

379
00:25:13,345 --> 00:25:14,546
<i>and watching you…</i>

380
00:25:16,081 --> 00:25:17,215
<i>I came to understand…</i>

381
00:25:19,050 --> 00:25:21,219
Kosei Neo as a person.

382
00:25:24,856 --> 00:25:26,424
Don't you think

383
00:25:27,792 --> 00:25:29,394
you've got something wrong?

384
00:25:32,264 --> 00:25:35,133
I've been doing the same as you.

385
00:25:38,069 --> 00:25:41,406
Using your diaries
and video clips as clues,

386
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:44,576
I've been playing the role of Kosei Neo.

387
00:25:49,781 --> 00:25:50,749
No way…

388
00:25:51,483 --> 00:25:53,718
If even you couldn't tell,

389
00:25:56,121 --> 00:25:59,758
I suppose I really am Kosei Neo by now.

390
00:26:00,892 --> 00:26:02,127
You're…

391
00:26:04,563 --> 00:26:05,864
Eito Nomoto.

392
00:26:14,072 --> 00:26:15,073
That's why

393
00:26:16,808 --> 00:26:18,543
you helped Akari Shopping Street.

394
00:26:19,578 --> 00:26:21,413
I intended to repay my debt

395
00:26:21,479 --> 00:26:24,082
- to Akari Shopping Street.
- Then why

396
00:26:25,417 --> 00:26:27,452
did you destroy where you grew up?

397
00:26:27,519 --> 00:26:30,288
I proposed the best terms possible!

398
00:26:30,355 --> 00:26:32,490
You should've known!

399
00:26:40,298 --> 00:26:42,033
After becoming Kosei Neo,

400
00:26:43,868 --> 00:26:45,870
I visited Akari Shopping Street
several times.

401
00:26:46,738 --> 00:26:47,872
Eito!

402
00:26:47,939 --> 00:26:49,808
You're the savior

403
00:26:49,874 --> 00:26:51,343
of Akari Shopping Street!

404
00:26:51,409 --> 00:26:54,646
<i>Eito Nomoto was there.</i>

405
00:26:57,215 --> 00:26:59,451
There was no place for me.

406
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:03,755
I had no choice but to be Kosei Neo.

407
00:27:05,390 --> 00:27:07,592
<i>And living as Kosei Neo,</i>

408
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:10,495
<i>I gradually lost track</i>

409
00:27:11,696 --> 00:27:13,298
<i>of who I was.</i>

410
00:27:15,467 --> 00:27:16,434
But

411
00:27:18,036 --> 00:27:20,672
you tried to be there for Sarasa.

412
00:27:22,173 --> 00:27:23,141
Wasn't…

413
00:27:24,075 --> 00:27:25,176
that…

414
00:27:26,678 --> 00:27:29,047
Eito Nomoto's feeling?

415
00:27:30,682 --> 00:27:31,516
Sarasa…

416
00:27:32,117 --> 00:27:33,551
Excuse me.

417
00:27:35,587 --> 00:27:37,922
<i>Everyone in the shopping street,</i>

418
00:27:38,723 --> 00:27:40,125
my dad, Eri…

419
00:27:40,191 --> 00:27:41,926
I can only feel sorry for you.

420
00:27:41,993 --> 00:27:43,795
10 billion yen.

421
00:27:43,862 --> 00:27:45,864
<i>…they all became distant.</i>

422
00:27:47,832 --> 00:27:48,700
But

423
00:27:49,901 --> 00:27:51,736
what you left behind

424
00:27:52,604 --> 00:27:54,739
spurred me on.

425
00:27:58,910 --> 00:28:00,745
The world is entertainment.

426
00:28:02,814 --> 00:28:05,417
Enjoy the game for all it's worth.

427
00:28:06,184 --> 00:28:09,554
Climbing to the top
is the meaning of life.

428
00:28:13,258 --> 00:28:14,726
Even if there are small sacrifices

429
00:28:14,793 --> 00:28:16,561
like the shopping street…

430
00:28:16,628 --> 00:28:19,531
If I act, I can save more people.

431
00:28:19,597 --> 00:28:21,099
That's what I told myself!

432
00:28:30,041 --> 00:28:31,076
I know.

433
00:28:34,746 --> 00:28:36,414
I was Kosei Neo too.

434
00:28:41,052 --> 00:28:43,188
Discarding the few

435
00:28:44,089 --> 00:28:46,057
to save the many…

436
00:28:47,459 --> 00:28:49,394
I believed that was right.

437
00:28:50,061 --> 00:28:50,962
But…

438
00:28:52,263 --> 00:28:53,631
no one understood.

439
00:28:57,469 --> 00:29:00,338
People don't understand
unless they're in that position.

440
00:29:02,273 --> 00:29:03,007
‎NEO TRADING

441
00:29:03,074 --> 00:29:04,309
<i>In my case,</i>

442
00:29:05,577 --> 00:29:08,613
<i>once I get revenge, it's all over.</i>

443
00:29:12,817 --> 00:29:15,019
Kosei Neo's life…

444
00:29:18,423 --> 00:29:19,424
was lonely.

445
00:29:23,862 --> 00:29:26,431
That's something only you and I
who have lived as Kosei Neo

446
00:29:26,498 --> 00:29:28,767
could ever understand.

447
00:29:30,935 --> 00:29:33,905
No one else could ever understand.

448
00:29:37,642 --> 00:29:39,310
It's the environment you're placed in,

449
00:29:40,845 --> 00:29:42,280
where you live,

450
00:29:43,114 --> 00:29:44,415
who you're with…

451
00:29:47,819 --> 00:29:49,821
People can change.

452
00:29:53,224 --> 00:29:55,560
As I lived as Eito Nomoto,

453
00:29:57,095 --> 00:29:59,063
<i>I came to care deeply for the people</i>

454
00:29:59,130 --> 00:30:02,700
<i>of Akari Shopping Street who kept making
the same mistakes over and over.</i>

455
00:30:04,202 --> 00:30:06,104
Those who look down from above

456
00:30:08,006 --> 00:30:09,874
and those who look up from below…

457
00:30:12,177 --> 00:30:13,678
They're all just people.

458
00:30:16,681 --> 00:30:19,350
I was certain I would reach the top.

459
00:30:20,685 --> 00:30:21,920
But

460
00:30:22,854 --> 00:30:24,556
the higher I climbed,

461
00:30:26,391 --> 00:30:27,892
<i>the less I could see the future.</i>

462
00:30:31,062 --> 00:30:33,298
You thought the same way?

463
00:30:36,901 --> 00:30:37,836
Yes.

464
00:30:38,770 --> 00:30:39,838
I thought the same way.

465
00:30:41,139 --> 00:30:42,473
I see.

466
00:30:44,843 --> 00:30:46,744
When I was Kosei Neo,

467
00:30:47,579 --> 00:30:49,681
I fell down those stone steps

468
00:30:50,315 --> 00:30:51,683
<i>and became Eito Nomoto.</i>

469
00:30:52,684 --> 00:30:53,918
<i>That day is today.</i>

470
00:30:54,752 --> 00:30:56,421
I've been searching all this time

471
00:30:57,188 --> 00:30:58,690
for who did it.

472
00:31:01,392 --> 00:31:02,460
Was it Tomono?

473
00:31:03,528 --> 00:31:04,696
No.

474
00:31:06,130 --> 00:31:08,466
I've arrived at a different answer.

475
00:31:10,201 --> 00:31:11,236
A different answer?

476
00:31:16,107 --> 00:31:18,309
The idea that someone pushed me…

477
00:31:20,144 --> 00:31:21,880
That was just my assumption.

478
00:31:23,715 --> 00:31:24,816
The truth is…

479
00:31:26,718 --> 00:31:29,687
like you, I felt the future was hopeless.

480
00:31:30,822 --> 00:31:32,156
Hopeless?

481
00:31:39,097 --> 00:31:41,499
Kosei Neo fell by his own hand.

482
00:31:50,408 --> 00:31:52,010
I don't want that for you.

483
00:31:55,513 --> 00:31:57,282
Talk to me.

484
00:31:57,348 --> 00:31:59,550
I want to talk more.

485
00:32:01,052 --> 00:32:02,654
The future can be changed.

486
00:32:11,996 --> 00:32:13,064
I'm…

487
00:32:17,335 --> 00:32:18,403
exhausted.

488
00:32:28,446 --> 00:32:29,914
Ow!

489
00:32:31,883 --> 00:32:32,850
Dad!

490
00:32:34,052 --> 00:32:35,253
Why?

491
00:32:39,424 --> 00:32:40,658
Why not!

492
00:32:42,427 --> 00:32:43,795
There's no reason.

493
00:32:50,101 --> 00:32:51,069
Maybe it's

494
00:32:52,136 --> 00:32:54,339
because you two look so alike.

495
00:33:02,513 --> 00:33:05,683
You've been strong all this time.

496
00:33:11,823 --> 00:33:12,690
Are you okay?

497
00:33:21,032 --> 00:33:22,233
You two…

498
00:33:23,568 --> 00:33:24,602
You'll be all right.

499
00:33:34,178 --> 00:33:36,547
<i>The future I know ends here.</i>

500
00:33:38,216 --> 00:33:41,019
<i>From here, the real future begins.</i>

501
00:33:42,854 --> 00:33:44,555
<i>What happens from here on out</i>

502
00:33:45,923 --> 00:33:47,759
<i>is beyond me.</i>

503
00:33:49,093 --> 00:33:49,961
<i>But</i>

504
00:33:50,995 --> 00:33:52,864
<i>I'm still here, still living.</i>

505
00:33:54,899 --> 00:33:57,468
<i>This novel said the price for using</i>

506
00:33:58,136 --> 00:34:01,005
<i>memories of the past is one's life…</i>

507
00:34:01,572 --> 00:34:02,974
<i>So it was fiction</i>

508
00:34:04,108 --> 00:34:05,510
<i>after all.</i>

509
00:34:07,045 --> 00:34:08,780
<i>Reality is far more ambiguous</i>

510
00:34:09,447 --> 00:34:10,915
<i>than any story.</i>

511
00:34:13,484 --> 00:34:15,119
What did you want to see me about?

512
00:34:15,953 --> 00:34:18,790
These are the NEOXIS company documents

513
00:34:18,856 --> 00:34:20,725
entrusted to me by Neo.

514
00:34:23,194 --> 00:34:24,495
And this states that

515
00:34:25,797 --> 00:34:29,233
Neo is stepping down as president

516
00:34:30,301 --> 00:34:32,804
and entrusting everything

517
00:34:33,538 --> 00:34:35,640
to his successor.

518
00:34:38,743 --> 00:34:41,979
He's resigning?

519
00:34:43,047 --> 00:34:46,117
I recommended you as his successor,

520
00:34:47,318 --> 00:34:48,920
but he declined.

521
00:34:49,887 --> 00:34:51,422
"Eito Nomoto

522
00:34:51,489 --> 00:34:53,291
should continue walking

523
00:34:53,357 --> 00:34:55,259
alongside the people
of the Akari Shopping Street."

524
00:34:55,927 --> 00:34:57,428
Those were his words.

525
00:34:59,897 --> 00:35:03,501
Neo has named Tomono

526
00:35:04,335 --> 00:35:06,270
as his successor.

527
00:35:10,374 --> 00:35:11,209
But

528
00:35:11,943 --> 00:35:13,511
why would he do this?

529
00:35:14,712 --> 00:35:16,581
I don't know either.

530
00:35:20,918 --> 00:35:26,224
Kosei Neo changed

531
00:35:27,859 --> 00:35:28,993
after meeting you.

532
00:35:39,504 --> 00:35:43,441
I'm Tatsuki Tomono,
and I have been appointed

533
00:35:43,508 --> 00:35:45,710
as chief executive officer and president.

534
00:35:45,776 --> 00:35:48,179
Returning to where it all began,

535
00:35:48,246 --> 00:35:51,149
I again feel the weight

536
00:35:51,215 --> 00:35:54,318
of this company

537
00:35:54,385 --> 00:35:56,187
and everything Neo built.

538
00:35:56,254 --> 00:36:00,725
As someone who was part
of NEOXIS's founding,

539
00:36:00,791 --> 00:36:02,426
I believe I understand the potential

540
00:36:02,493 --> 00:36:05,596
and responsibility this company holds

541
00:36:05,663 --> 00:36:08,032
more deeply than anyone.

542
00:36:08,099 --> 00:36:09,700
<i>With Kosei Neo stepping down</i>

543
00:36:09,767 --> 00:36:12,770
<i>as NEOXIS's president,</i>

544
00:36:12,837 --> 00:36:15,573
<i>his successor</i>

545
00:36:15,640 --> 00:36:18,176
<i>is Tatsuki Tomono, representative</i>

546
00:36:18,242 --> 00:36:20,845
<i>of the humanitarian support company
Friends Earth Support.</i>

547
00:36:21,579 --> 00:36:23,581
<i>In other news, stock and exchange rate--</i>

548
00:36:24,415 --> 00:36:27,351
Hey! Tomono is incredible!

549
00:36:27,418 --> 00:36:29,620
- Quite the rise.
- Right.

550
00:36:29,687 --> 00:36:32,123
I hope this means NEOXIS will change too.

551
00:36:32,190 --> 00:36:33,691
Does that mean Eri is going to be

552
00:36:33,758 --> 00:36:36,093
a president's wife?

553
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:38,629
You're right.

554
00:36:38,696 --> 00:36:40,097
We have to celebrate.

555
00:36:40,164 --> 00:36:41,999
They're coming after the press conference.

556
00:36:42,066 --> 00:36:45,102
- Oh!
- Oh. I'll fry up croquettes and cutlets.

557
00:36:45,169 --> 00:36:47,004
- Nice!
- Sarasa, can you help?

558
00:36:47,071 --> 00:36:48,539
Of course.

559
00:36:48,606 --> 00:36:50,007
Actually,

560
00:36:50,074 --> 00:36:51,909
I have some news of my own.

561
00:36:51,976 --> 00:36:53,211
- News?
- Huh?

562
00:36:56,781 --> 00:36:57,848
This!

563
00:36:58,549 --> 00:36:59,450
What is this?

564
00:36:59,517 --> 00:37:01,752
The floor plan
for Super Soman's Arakawa store.

565
00:37:01,819 --> 00:37:03,754
Why do you have that?

566
00:37:04,322 --> 00:37:07,124
NEOXIS, who owns this property,
is transferring it

567
00:37:07,191 --> 00:37:10,027
to Akari Shopping Street Co., Ltd.

568
00:37:10,595 --> 00:37:13,331
- Huh?
- President Neo

569
00:37:13,397 --> 00:37:14,799
entrusted it to Tomono.

570
00:37:15,900 --> 00:37:17,501
- Huh?
- Huh?

571
00:37:17,568 --> 00:37:18,302
- Huh?
- Hey!

572
00:37:18,369 --> 00:37:23,307
Whether to use
the existing building or rebuild it

573
00:37:23,374 --> 00:37:24,709
is entirely up to you, Dad.

574
00:37:24,775 --> 00:37:26,644
- Huh?
- Hey!

575
00:37:26,711 --> 00:37:29,247
Hey!

576
00:37:29,313 --> 00:37:31,148
Hey!

577
00:37:31,215 --> 00:37:33,217
What is happening right now?!

578
00:37:33,284 --> 00:37:35,186
Wait!

579
00:37:35,820 --> 00:37:38,489
We get to work

580
00:37:38,556 --> 00:37:40,424
together again?

581
00:37:40,491 --> 00:37:42,627
Dad!

582
00:37:42,693 --> 00:37:43,894
Hey, Dad!

583
00:37:43,961 --> 00:37:46,163
- It hurts!
- Are you okay?

584
00:37:46,230 --> 00:37:48,032
This time it's really not a dream!

585
00:37:49,433 --> 00:37:50,835
Let's contact those who left!

586
00:37:50,901 --> 00:37:52,870
- Right. Inose, Shikano, and Chono too.
- Yeah.

587
00:37:52,937 --> 00:37:56,307
- And Kayo. Anyone who wants to come back.
- Yeah.

588
00:37:56,374 --> 00:37:58,342
Let's all figure out the future together!

589
00:37:58,409 --> 00:38:00,511
- Yeah!
- We're counting on you, Eito.

590
00:38:00,578 --> 00:38:03,180
I'm going for it!
Once I decide, I never back down!

591
00:38:03,247 --> 00:38:05,349
Yeah!

592
00:38:05,416 --> 00:38:07,418
I'm so happy!

593
00:38:08,252 --> 00:38:10,655
Sarasa? What's wrong?

594
00:38:13,424 --> 00:38:14,825
My painting

595
00:38:14,892 --> 00:38:16,961
at the Noble Art Competition…

596
00:38:18,095 --> 00:38:19,897
It won the grand prize!

597
00:38:19,964 --> 00:38:24,368
- You won?!
- Yeah!

598
00:38:24,435 --> 00:38:27,805
Yeah! Wow!

599
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:31,909
Ow!

600
00:38:31,976 --> 00:38:34,879
- What happened?
- Are you okay?

601
00:38:34,945 --> 00:38:38,282
- I'm fine.
- Is your head okay?

602
00:38:38,349 --> 00:38:41,485
- Congratulations!
- Thanks!

603
00:38:41,552 --> 00:38:44,388
Thanks! Thanks to everyone!

604
00:38:47,558 --> 00:38:50,194
It always feels so good here,
no matter when we come.

605
00:38:53,698 --> 00:38:56,033
I'm glad to be here.

606
00:38:57,668 --> 00:38:59,770
I had convinced myself
I could die at any moment.

607
00:39:01,772 --> 00:39:05,109
But when I think about it,

608
00:39:06,110 --> 00:39:10,314
everyone lives knowing any day
could be their last.

609
00:39:10,381 --> 00:39:11,482
That's what I thought.

610
00:39:12,650 --> 00:39:14,552
I'm nothing special.

611
00:39:17,855 --> 00:39:18,989
For now,

612
00:39:21,025 --> 00:39:24,161
I'm just going to live my life.

613
00:39:25,896 --> 00:39:26,764
Yeah.

614
00:39:27,531 --> 00:39:28,866
I couldn't agree more.

615
00:39:33,704 --> 00:39:34,772
Hey!

616
00:39:36,340 --> 00:39:37,842
Can I ask you one more time?

617
00:39:41,979 --> 00:39:43,414
Who are you?

618
00:39:46,584 --> 00:39:49,353
You're not the Eito I know…

619
00:39:51,021 --> 00:39:53,758
and not the Kosei Neo I know either.

620
00:40:05,302 --> 00:40:06,837
I guess it doesn't matter.

621
00:40:10,508 --> 00:40:11,575
Because right now,

622
00:40:12,710 --> 00:40:14,945
the person in front of me…

623
00:40:17,681 --> 00:40:18,849
is you.

624
00:40:22,820 --> 00:40:24,288
I'm glad I was born into this world.

625
00:40:45,776 --> 00:40:46,977
<i>Maybe God</i>

626
00:40:47,678 --> 00:40:49,713
<i>likes to keep things balanced.</i>

627
00:40:51,182 --> 00:40:53,317
<i>Good things and bad things</i>

628
00:40:54,285 --> 00:40:56,487
<i>always seem to take turns.</i>

629
00:40:59,356 --> 00:41:00,357
<i>Perhaps</i>

630
00:41:01,225 --> 00:41:03,994
<i>too many good things happened today.</i>

631
00:41:12,937 --> 00:41:16,740
No way! Just having Sarasa's painting
in the bookshop makes it

632
00:41:16,807 --> 00:41:19,443
- a cozy spot.
- The sewing class is amazing too.

633
00:41:19,510 --> 00:41:22,746
Things came together
just the way Eito had envisioned.

634
00:41:22,813 --> 00:41:25,382
He really thought of everything for us.

635
00:41:25,449 --> 00:41:27,518
Business plans are great and all,

636
00:41:27,585 --> 00:41:29,153
but what about the spring festival?

637
00:41:29,220 --> 00:41:32,356
I'd love that.
Now that everyone's back together.

638
00:41:32,423 --> 00:41:34,492
- Yeah!
- What about money?

639
00:41:34,558 --> 00:41:36,227
With a sponsor, we could do it.

640
00:41:36,293 --> 00:41:37,928
Right, Mr. President?

641
00:41:38,696 --> 00:41:40,197
There it is!

642
00:41:41,665 --> 00:41:43,067
I'll look into it favorably.

643
00:41:43,133 --> 00:41:45,402
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

644
00:41:47,705 --> 00:41:50,207
- Okay!
- Oh!

645
00:41:50,274 --> 00:41:52,443
It's okay!

646
00:41:52,510 --> 00:41:56,447
The croquettes and cutlets are ready!

647
00:41:56,514 --> 00:42:00,384
Here! We have sweet potato chips!

648
00:42:00,451 --> 00:42:03,254
Everything Eito loves!

649
00:42:03,320 --> 00:42:05,289
- Here, Mr. President!
- You're right.

650
00:42:05,356 --> 00:42:08,926
- Want some?
- Thank you!

651
00:42:08,993 --> 00:42:10,761
- Were they freshly made?
- They're good!

652
00:42:11,562 --> 00:42:15,666
The fact that we're all here like this
is because of Eito.

653
00:42:15,733 --> 00:42:17,234
You're right.

654
00:42:18,602 --> 00:42:21,071
Eito was always…

655
00:42:23,140 --> 00:42:24,475
Our

656
00:42:26,076 --> 00:42:27,645
hero.

657
00:42:37,888 --> 00:42:39,790
‎CONGRATS! SARASA IKETANI
‎GOLD AWARD

658
00:43:29,273 --> 00:43:31,208
DON'T LET COVID WIN! MASS PRODUCTION PLAN
FOR ORIGINAL MERCHANDISE!

659
00:44:15,719 --> 00:44:18,989
‎THIS DRAMA IS A WORK OF FICTION

660
00:44:19,056 --> 00:44:20,024
Subtitle translation by: Ken Nishizaki
